SEARCH
Package functional.annotations

Annotation Interface TestDataAnnotation

@Retention(RUNTIME) @Target(METHOD) public @interface TestDataAnnotation
A custom annotation used to define test data properties for TestNG test methods. This annotation allows specifying the Google Sheet details and data provider behavior.

  • Optional Element Summary

    Optional Elements
    Modifier and Type
    Optional Element
    Description
    boolean
    isNoDataProvider
    Flag to indicate whether a data provider should be used or not.
    String
    rowNumber
    Specifies a specific row number or range of rows in the sheet to use for test data.
    String
    sheetId
    Specifies the ID of the Google Sheet document from which to retrieve test data.
    String
    sheetName
    Specifies the name of the sheet in the Google Sheet document from which to retrieve test data.

  • Element Details

    • sheetName

      String sheetName
      Specifies the name of the sheet in the Google Sheet document from which to retrieve test data.
      Returns:
      The name of the sheet.
      Default:
      ""

    • sheetId

      String sheetId
      Specifies the ID of the Google Sheet document from which to retrieve test data.
      Returns:
      The ID of the Google Sheet.
      Default:
      ""

    • isNoDataProvider

      boolean isNoDataProvider
      Flag to indicate whether a data provider should be used or not. If set to true, no data provider will be used for the test method.
      Returns:
      True if no data provider is to be used, false otherwise.
      Default:
      false

    • rowNumber

      String rowNumber
      Specifies a specific row number or range of rows in the sheet to use for test data. Default is "All", which means all rows are considered.
      Returns:
      The row number or range as a string.
      Default:
      "All"
